post:
I just found out they have a new plan called "Warm-Up". It costs 60RUB which, [according to XE](http://www.xe.com/currencyconverter/convert/?Amount=60&amp;From=RUB&amp;To=USD), is about $1.76.

Full specs:

* `CPU: 1 Core` 
* `RAM: 256 MB` 
* `HDD: 10 GB`
* `BW:  Unlimited @ 100Mbps`

This is a limited stock offer. They're planning to sell 1000 VPSes only.

Terms and conditions apply (_for this plan_):

* No ISPmanager[1];
* No promotions and discounts apply for this plan;
* You can't order any add-ons for this plan;
* Their free DNS is not available for this plan;
* No moneyback;

UPD: (translation by @rm_)

* VM type is OpenVZ;
* Game servers are forbidden on this plan;
* Abusers will be kicked out (with the provider determining in their sole discretion what amounts to "abuse");
* No SLA or guarantee of any kind whatsoever.

Full list and more invo available here: http://firstvds.ru/products/vds_vps_cheap

[1]. ISPmanager is honestly the best server control panel I've ever used. It's developed by ISPserver, the company behind FirstVDS. Though I guess lack of the control panel should not be a turndown for most of the LET users.

FirstVDS has been in business [since late 2002](http://web.archive.org/web/20030201102245/http://firstvds.ru/ru/home/index.html). I've been using their services for 6 years already. Except for the links, I am not affiliated with this company. I was lucky enough to get on a node where I've experienced little to no network/availability issues. Because of that positive experience I was recommending the company to most of my friends and people I was working with, but some of them actually did experience unavailability issues. Not for long though, so I think it's kind of acceptable for a low-end budget service.

_They also offer some other plans, starting from ~$4.37 for 512MB/30GB/Unlim VPS. You can get a 25% one-time discount on those plans if you use [my affiliate link](http://bit.ly/FirstVDSplans)._
